name: Tyler Johnson
about:
At Cal Poly SLO, my role as a Lecturer fuses academic research with the dynamic world of Comparative Politics and Political Economics, where I guide and inspire over 35 undergraduates every quarter. The intersection of education and policy analysis is where I thrive, leveraging my MSc in Comparative Politics to craft original learning experiences and engage students deeply in the subject matter. 

My expertise, honed through hands-on event coordination, research, and analytical rigor, is complemented by a strong foundation in Chinese language and culture. This unique blend of skills fuels my commitment to fostering global understanding and political literacy, positioning me as a valuable asset for organizations seeking to navigate the complexities of international relations and political dynamics.
